Class: Solution
Method: isValid(self, n: int) -> bool

# Objective:
Return True if the integer `n` satisfies ALL of the following 1 independent constraints:
1. n is greater than 2
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "isValid")
  (signature ((n int)) bool)
  (constraints
    (constraint "The input n must be an integer.")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Determine if the integer n satisfies all specified constraints.")
    (rule "Return True if n is greater than 2.")
    (return "True if all constraints are satisfied, otherwise False.")
  )
)
generated_code:
# solution.py
from typing import bool

class Solution:
    def isValid(self, n: int) -> bool:
        """
        Determine if the integer n satisfies all specified constraints.

        Parameters:
        n (int): The input integer to validate.

        Returns:
        bool: True if n is greater than 2, otherwise False.
        """
        return n > 2
